724079f-a.title: Manhattan: Washington Street - Rector Street
724079f-a.text:
Washington Street, east side, north from (No. 101, axtreme right),
Rector Street, showing an early view of this downtown area which has
undergone many changes. The most radical was the replacement of the
double, white front tenement (No. 105-107) by the Bowling Green
Neighborhood House. The tenement adjacent to same became St. Georges
Roman Catholic Church about the same time (about 19277). For views of
both structures mentioned see files under their respective addresses.
April 1911.
Geo. L. Balgue.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
